00:28:02.130 --> 00:28:04.880
The Stanford team is putting its hopes in a set of

00:28:04.880 --> 00:28:09.500
off-the-shelf lasers linked through software to a simple video camera.

00:28:09.500 --> 00:28:15.080
The camera can see all the way to the horizon.

00:28:15.080 --> 00:28:19.640
The trick is to give Stanley some way to distinguish the road in the video image.

00:28:19.640 --> 00:28:20.340
So this is just one laser. You can see it there steer the vehicle.

00:28:20.340 --> 00:28:27.875
Stanley's lasers pinpoint smooth terrain right in front of the vehicle.

00:28:27.875 --> 00:28:30.865
